# Netlify — use MCP

When the **netlify** MCP server is enabled in Cursor, use it first for Netlify work. Do not rely on `netlify` CLI or raw curl unless MCP is unavailable or the user asks for CLI.

## Setup (required for MCP)

1. `cp .env.netlify.example .env.netlify` and add a [personal access token](https://app.netlify.com/user/applications#personal-access-tokens).
2. `pnpm netlify:connect` (links canonical site).
3. Restart Cursor or reload MCP so `netlify` appears in available servers.

Config: `.cursor/mcp.json` → `scripts/mcp-netlify.sh` (loads `.env.netlify`).

## Canonical site (only one)

- **Keep:** `dazzling-pithivier-e119b1` (production `cryptopay.sale`; see `NETLIFY_SITE_ID` in `scripts/lib/netlify-site.sh`).
- **Delete extras:** e.g. a second site from Git import named `Crypto-Pay`.
- Production domain: `cryptopay.sale` → must match `NETLIFY_SITE_HOSTNAME` in `.env.porkbun`.

## MCP workflow for audits / duplicates

1. `list-sites` (or resource `netlify://sites`) — list all sites.
2. `get-site-info` / site overview — confirm custom domain, repo `photospheremedia/Crypto-Pay`, deploy settings.
3. Recommend **KEEP** the highest-match site; **delete** others via `delete-site` only after user confirms.
4. Do not create a new site if `crypto-pay-portal` already exists.

## Deploys

- Prefer MCP deploy/build tools when available.
- GitHub Actions: `.github/workflows/netlify.yml` (single workflow).
- Avoid triple deploy: disable Netlify UI “build on push” if using Actions.

## Fallback

If MCP server is missing: `pnpm netlify:audit` (API script) or `pnpm exec netlify sites:list` after `pnpm netlify:connect`.
